In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires—
'authorized officer' means any officer of the Agency authorized in writing by the Chief Executive under section 7;
'Chief Executive' means the Chief Executive of the National Cyber Security Agency appointed under section 6;
'Committee' means the National Cyber Security Committee established under section 8;
'computer' means an electronic, magnetic, optical, electrochemical, or other data processing device, or a group of such interconnected or related devices, performing logical, arithmetic, storage and display functions, and includes any data storage facility or communications facility directly related to or operating in conjunction with such device or group of such interconnected or related devices;
'cyber security' means the state in which a computer, computer system, network, data, software application, computer program or other configurable computing resource is protected from cyber security threats;
'cyber security incident' means any act or activity carried out without authorization on a computer, computer system, network, data, software application, computer program or other configurable computing resource that jeopardizes or adversely affects its cyber security, including unauthorized access, interference, interception, denial of service, data breach, system compromise or exploitation of vulnerability;
'cyber security risk assessment' means a systematic process for identifying, analyzing and evaluating cyber security risks;
'cyber security service' means a service that is provided for the purpose of protecting or responding to a cyber security threat to a computer, computer system, network, data, software application, computer program or other configurable computing resource, and includes managed security operations centre monitoring service, penetration testing service, cyber security incident response service, and any other service as may be prescribed;
'cyber security service provider' means any person who provides a cyber security service;
'cyber security threat' means any act, omission, activity, or state of affairs that may jeopardize or adversely affect the cyber security of a computer, computer system, network, data, software application, computer program or other configurable computing resource;
'data' means representations of information or concepts that are being prepared or have been prepared in a form suitable for use in a computer;
'national critical information infrastructure' means any computer or computer system, which the disruption, destruction, degradation or compromise of, or unauthorized access to, would have a debilitating impact on the delivery of a service essential to the security, defence, foreign relations, economy, public health, public safety, or public order of Malaysia, or on the ability of the Federal Government or any State Government to carry out its functions effectively;
'NCII entity' means an entity designated as an NCII entity under section 17;
'NCII sector' means any sector specified in the Schedule;
'NCII sector lead' means a Government Entity designated as an NCII sector lead under section 17;
'network' means a system of two or more computers that are interconnected by telecommunications links;
'prescribed' means prescribed by the Minister by regulations made under this Act.
